<h1 class='track-pos' id='step-2-create-api-key'>Step 2 &#8211; Create API Key</h1>
<p>We&#8217;ll need to generate an API Key so that Media Cloud can access the Space. Navigate to the&nbsp;<strong>API</strong>&nbsp;section, scroll down to&nbsp;<strong>Space access keys</strong>&nbsp;and click on&nbsp;<strong>Generate New Key</strong>.</p>
<figure class="wp-block-image"><img src="https://i.imgur.com/gyG1EEW.png" alt="image.png"/></figure>
<h3 class='track-pos' id='step-2-1-key-properties'>Step 2.1 &#8211; Key Properties</h3>
<p>Once you click&nbsp;<strong>Generate New Key</strong>, you&#8217;ll need to give the key a name and click on the checkmark next to it.</p>
<figure class="wp-block-image"><img src="https://i.imgur.com/3PvUVEP.png" alt="image.png"/></figure>
<p>DigitalOcean will then generate a new key and display it to you. It will only display this to you once, so you should copy down the Key and the Secret now as we will be using it later.</p>
<figure class="wp-block-image"><img src="https://i.imgur.com/9CfZMRo.png" alt="image.png"/></figure>
